						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone near Kere-kōḍi Siddappa temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift made by <hi rend="bold">Banavāji Sāmarāya</hi> to <hi rend="bold">Nāgaṇa-Bhaṭṭa</hi> (son of) <hi rend="bold">Aṇṇi-Bhaṭṭa,</hi> the village priest of <hi rend="bold">Vijāpura.</hi> The characters belong to about the <hi rend="bold">16-17th century A.D.</hi></p>						

